<%# Phase 26 — 01d. Layout-level webhook help modal.

    The Slack + Discord pane `[help]` links open this modal instead of
    navigating. The dialog hosts a Turbo Frame
    (`webhook_help_modal_frame`); the Stimulus `webhook-help-modal`
    controller (mounted on `<body>`) sets the frame's `src` to
    `/settings/webhooks/help/<provider>` on open. The controller's
    `show` action renders the Markdown-rendered guide inside a
    matching `<turbo-frame>` so Turbo swaps in the content.

    Closing semantics mirror the project's other layout-level dialogs
    (notifications, search, IGDB search) AND the canonical
    `.tui-dialog-frame` adopters (help overlay, about dialog):
      - Esc — native <dialog> Escape handling + an explicit keydown
        guard on the controller. The `[Esc] to close` hint sits on
        the top-right of the dialog border (FB-43 adoption of the
        canonical `.tui-dialog-frame` pattern).
      - Backdrop click — `clickOutside` action.

    No in-content `[close]` bracketed link (FB-43 dropped both the
    bottom-of-fragment muted close and the wrapper-level close to leave
    Esc + backdrop click as the single dismissal grammar that matches
    the help overlay + about dialog).

    No JS `confirm()` / `alert()` / `prompt()` and no
    `data-turbo-confirm` (CLAUDE.md hard rule). %>
<%# The help modal is wider than the other dialog variants because it
    hosts multi-paragraph prose, code blocks, and tables (Troubleshooting).
    `pane-dialog` clamps to 600px, `confirm-modal` to 420px — neither is
    enough room for the rendered guide without horizontal scroll. We set
    width inline so the modal stays self-contained and we don't have to
    introduce another class variant.

    `overflow-x: hidden` + `overflow-wrap: anywhere` on the inner content
    keeps long webhook-URL strings from blowing the layout out
    horizontally; they wrap inside the code block instead.

    FB-43 (2026-05-20). The dialog adopts the canonical `.tui-dialog-frame`
    pattern (FB-53 / FB-65): a 1px hairline outer border with the title
    text sitting ON the top border at the corners.

    FB-103 (2026-05-20). The title text now reflects the per-brand
    identity directly (`Slack webhook setup` / `Discord webhook setup`)
    so the in-body `<h1>` could be dropped from the markdown sources
    (no more duplicate title — border title and body title were
    redundant). Because the dialog frame lives in the layout (rendered
    once) and the provider is only known on the click that opens it,
    the title is driven from data-attributes:
      - `data-webhook-help-modal-title-slack-value` — Slack brand title
      - `data-webhook-help-modal-title-discord-value` — Discord brand title
    The Stimulus controller's `open()` action reads the
    provider-specific value and rewrites the `__title-left` span
    contents before calling `showModal()`. The server-rendered initial
    text is the generic `webhook help` fallback in case the controller
    hasn't booted yet.

    The previous in-fragment `Tui::FramedPanelComponent` wrap (with its
    own border + brand-suffixed title) and the dual bottom `[close]`
    bracketed links are gone; Esc + backdrop click + the title-right
    hint are the only dismissal paths.

    Inner padded wrapper keeps the scroll behavior intact but switches
    its padding to `0 14px 12px` (the `.tui-dialog-frame` rule already
    contributes `padding: 16px 10px 12px` on the outer `<dialog>`, so
    the wrapper only needs horizontal breathing room for the rendered
    prose). %>
<dialog id="webhook-help-modal"
        class="pane-dialog webhook-help-modal tui-dialog-frame"
        style="max-width: 900px; width: min(900px, 92vw);"
        data-webhook-help-title-slack="<%= t("settings.webhooks.help.brand_title", brand: "Slack") %>"
        data-webhook-help-title-discord="<%= t("settings.webhooks.help.brand_title", brand: "Discord") %>"
        data-action="click->webhook-help-modal#clickOutside keydown->webhook-help-modal#keydown"
        data-modal-actions-key="webhook_help">
  <span class="tui-dialog-frame__title-left" data-webhook-help-title><%= t("settings.webhooks.help.title") %></span>
  <span class="tui-dialog-frame__title-right">[<%= t("keys.esc") %>] <%= t("settings.webhooks.help.esc_close_suffix") %></span>
  <div class="webhook-help-modal__inner" style="padding: 0 14px 4px; max-height: 80vh; overflow-y: auto; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-wrap: break-word;">
    <%= turbo_frame_tag "webhook_help_modal_frame", src: nil, loading: "lazy" %>
  </div>
</dialog>
